<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="ida9957132-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s2638"><num value="2638">§ 2638.</num><heading> Transportation of civilian clothing of enlisted members</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary of the military department concerned may provide for the transportation of the civilian clothing of any person entering the armed forces as an enlisted member to the member’s home of record.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="ida9957133-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/98/525/tXIV/s1401/j/1">Pub. L. 98–525, title XIV, § 1401(j)(1)</ref>, <date date="1984-10-19">Oct. 19, 1984</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/98/2620">98 Stat. 2620</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="ida9957134-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5">
